Type: Presentation
Package: parse-dont-pray
Title: Parse, Don't Pray: The Case for Data Validation
Version: 1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Indrajeet", "Patil", , "patilindrajeet.science@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1995-6531", Twitter = "@patilindrajeets"))
Description: This presentation explores the benefits of using data
    validation libraries like Pydantic (Python) and Zod (TypeScript) to
    create robust, maintainable applications. It covers benefits across
    readability, runtime behavior, typing, testing, security, and
    developer experience. This is not a package, and the DESCRIPTION file
    is included to make it easier to install required packages in GitHub
    action workflows.
